My amazing parents have blessed my life with love , kindness, understanding and support. As they get older I realize that every moment is a gift . I tell them and show them how much I love them and how grateful I am every day. My dad talked back to the screen on numerous occasions during the premiere of #creed3 and cheered the fight scenes . He loved every second of it ! My mother looked over at me every time I appeared on the screen, her eyes sparkled with joy. My mother struggles with her memory these days but she was very present and enjoying it all , including her time with glam! I am nothing without these two extraordinary humans. Success means nothing without the love and support of your loved ones. I thank God for allowing my parents to witness moments like these . For years they watched me struggle within an industry that failed to see me. They witness my disappointment every time I didn’t get that role . They prayed over me , wiped my tears and believed in me. They also worried when they saw me hit rock bottom over a decade ago . So we celebrate the wins big and small…Here we are . Grateful, hopeful and all dressed up !! My dad says he is now at peace knowing I’m good. Although I am still working to achieve more I am beyond thankful they’ve witness some pretty big wins!! #family #familia #teamleyva #actorslife #daughter #movie #creed3 #godisgood #moretocome #therearenosmallrolesonlysmallactors #afrolatina #proud #love #cuba #dominicanrepublic

The people , the experience, the lessons , the art , the time. We gave it all! Thank you for supporting us! We had no idea who would watch but we knew it was special…. Turns out the world watched and the love was more than we expected. 10 years ! Thank you to our fans ! Thank you to this cast , the crew , background actors , our families for the ride! This was magical … it’s easy to forget when things outside of our control get in the way … but one thing is true … magic like this doesn’t happen often. I am grateful for it all. Full of emotions today ! My life forever changed with these people. Some of us still communicate maybe not as often but the LOVE remains even from a distance . What a ride ! Thank you @jennifer_euston_casting forever. #oitnb #gloriamendoza #netflix #foreverorange🍊

Mr Ron Cephas Jones, the coolest of all cats ! The poet, the actor , the father , a friend . I met Ron when I was 18 years old fresh out of high school. My first job as a teaching artist . He was a head counselor of the program and he was tall, kind, talented, and so incredibly cool! One thing I knew immediately was that he was a father to a little girl that he loved beyond words. His “ brown eyes” , a poem he shared about Jasmine. It was clear she was his heart !  Ron was a poet making his rounds not really working much as an actor in those days but he always smiled and never seemed jaded by the struggle. He encouraged me to dream big . His talks were always as if you were his equal . With a soft yet powerful voice he always made you stop and listen. He didn’t just talk to hear himself , he had wisdom to share .  Hearing the news of his passing has left an entire community of people in pain. I will rejoice in knowing that Ron got to show the world all his talent and heart . Years later after our first meeting in nyc and working together for years , both struggling actors , he made it . He received all his flowers . But most importantly, he saw his “ brown eyes” hit it big ! @jazzy_joness you have the coolest angel watching over you now. I will forever remember that smile and the day we ran into each other in some fancy event years later… we both stopped ,he put his hands together , said my name and that’s all that was needed. We both knew in that moment the journey we both had taken , the years of struggle in nyc to that moment . We hugged and then had a real good laugh as if to say “ can you believe this”!
Ron, my heart breaks today because I know you had so much more to give . I thank you for sharing your art , your humanity and your heart with us. Much love always , rest in peace my dear friend . 💙🙏🏽 #riproncephasjones

Last two days … I’ve had to leave behind my sweats and tshirt look . Big rooms , lots of people , the industry parties , cameras , red carpets …. Are challenging for me . Yeah I show up and smile but leading up to these moments is hard . Extremely. I’m grateful for having some good friends to lean on !! Being out and about is part of the business. For someone like me it causes me great anxiety and insecurities. Why share this? Well why not! It’s my truth and perhaps someone out there relates! I LOVE being an actor ! There is a big difference from performing and showing up as yourself to these events . Take care of yourself ! Take moments to regroup and breathe….. and thank you to those that show me so much love ! Random kind words and hugs really are heaven sent !! Much love !!❤️
This past year had some challenges but also MANY blessings and a few surprises !! Praying for health, peace , abundance and laughter!! Con mucho mucho amor💋 thanks 2023…. Let’s goooooooo2024🌟⭐️💫
